==English==
===[[onomatopoeia]]===
'''Grr''', '''grrrr''', '''grrrrrrrrrr''' etc. with as many 'r's as necessary to best mimic the length or ferocity of the growl
# '''Phonetic Slang'''. A word most frequently used in textual communications ([[email]], [[IRC]], [[w:USENET|USENET]], and so on) to represent that the user is "growling", thus [[mimic]]ing the sound of an [[animal]] which is [[anger]]ed or otherwise [[upset]].
